But most chanters are 'scared' to see a tank pulling 8-20 mobs at you. <br>
Get them over that fear and you have a fun time.<br>
It seemed that it took along time to get my guild to AE, <br>
now we &quot;ae&quot; everything. (this was about last year.)<br>
(King,Qween of Chardok, Temple of Fear, 2nd Island of sky are just some examples.)<br>
<br>
Heres some 'tips' that i've found<br>
For the chanters out there:<br>
-Load as many stuns so that you dont have any downtime waiting for the stuns to refresh. <br>
If you have to &quot;wait&quot; for your stun to refresh, you are going to get hit. <br>
<br>
For the Wizards:<br>
-Load 2 PB ae's (the ones over level 50) and chain cast them as fast as possible. <br>
-Use Jyll's pulse to interrupt/stun briefly (this spell also helps to get the mobs off the chanter.)<br>
If the wizards dont chain cast PB's the chanter will get hit more. If chanters die &quot;you&quot; die.<br>
<br>
For the puller:<br>
Best way is to &quot;invs&quot; the tank have them go out and &quot;find&quot; a bunch to pull. The tank MUST pull more then 5 mobs. 8-10 seem to be a perfect number in order for the tank to be able to make it back alive.<br>
<br>
For the healer:<br>
Yes, Clerics can AE too! with a 'good' Ae group, the cleric will only have to heal the tank &quot;once&quot; per pull, he'll be FM most the time, so why not have him AE too!<br>
<br>
General Tips:<br>
-If you only have 1-2 mobs, the chanter can mez OR chain stun them until the tank can pull more.<br>
-Make sure the wizards are FM before you pull.<br>
-Runes saves lives, runes/manashields can also prevent spell interruptions.<br>
<br>
Good Places to AE:<br>
-Karnors Basement<br>
-Chardok<br>
-Seb Disco Area and chief<br>
-The Hole (careful some mobs are unstunable/Unmezable, ie. <br>
golems)<br>
-DN (the traps) (about .5 to 1 blue per trap)<br>
&quot;any outdoor area with lots of mobs&quot;<br>
BW<br>
Raptors in TD<br>
DL<br>
<br>
&quot;There is nothing like getting half a blue bubble of exp per pull.&quot;<br>
<br>
-Graffy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/utervalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tervalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(12/3/01 2:58:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOE Chanters?</span><hr size=1> I am always good for an AOE group...<br>
